{"id":868149,"guid":"D9047D50330311EABDAD4DE020724EBD","previous_id":null,"previous_guid":null,"modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"92D8941CE4AA4823841E40F0B8353F6C","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Preparation of single-cell suspension "}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"C91D01D0A5B942E396A9AFCBF079EF65","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><ol style = \"list-style-type: decimal;\"><\/ol><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":3600,"critical":[],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":868151,"guid":"F63FDB80330311EABDAD4DE020724EBD","previous_id":868149,"previous_guid":"D9047D50330311EABDAD4DE020724EBD","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"1F56592A294E459D897CF2F3DF0BE676","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DAPI staining"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"F3A868985B654FAD8BD4853B5C611613","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><ol style = \"list-style-type: decimal;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Resuspend the dissociated cells in 400 \u00b5l cell culture media (e.g RPMI, DMEM) supplemented with 2.5% FBS and 0.1 mg\/ml DAPI dye. Aim for dilution of 500-2000 cells\/\u00b5l.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Incubate on ice for 5 min.<\/li><\/ol><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":300,"critical":[],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":868153,"guid":"05C56610330411EABDAD4DE020724EBD","previous_id":868151,"previous_guid":"F63FDB80330311EABDAD4DE020724EBD","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E0C87D9D490F4972A5BFB6F847C119CB","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"FACS sorting"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"4821C0D819554FE5848346E82E3D9249","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><ol style = \"list-style-type: decimal;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Add 400 \u00b5l of Bambanker preservation media in a 15 ml FACS collection tube.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">FACS-sort DAPI negative (live-cells) directly into the preservation media.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Collect >200,000 cells ideally, or 50,000 cells at a minimum.<\/li><\/ol><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"D9BB69084B7B43DF8D932B03A5C9EFA5","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">NOTE:<\/span><span> The preservation medium will get diluted by the FACS buffer during sorting. Avoid diluting more than 50%.<\/span><\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":1800,"critical":[],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":868154,"guid":"0B3C7A20330411EABDAD4DE020724EBD","previous_id":868153,"previous_guid":"05C56610330411EABDAD4DE020724EBD","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"C4141C704E2D47D396736A5EB8BC13B3","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Concentrating cell suspension"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"DCB8B02647354C86BFEB13AE48C37A22","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><ol style = \"list-style-type: decimal;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Transfer the FACS-sorted cell suspension into a 1.5 ml LoProtein Bind tube, but do not exceed 500 \u00b5l volume. If the sorted suspension constitutes more than 0.5 ml, then divide the solution into two tubes (e.g. each tube 400 \u00b5l). <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Transfer the tubes to a swinging bucket centrifuge and spin down at <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\"><a href=\"#\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\"> <\/span><\/a><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\"> <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">NOTE<\/span><span>: For centrifugation in a swinging bucket centrifuge place 1.5 ml tubes inside a 50 mL Falcon tube.<\/span><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">After centrifugation is complete, remove the medium without disrupting the pellet leaving ~20 \u00b5l of supernatant in the tube.  <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Dilute the cells with the preservation medium down to 1000-2000 cell\/\u00b5l. Use the FACS quantification as a guide, but keep in mind that these numbers are often inflated.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Gently resuspend the cells using a 1000 \u00b5l or 200 \u00b5l pipette. Do not leave cell clumps behind.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">At this step, one would typically expect to have 50-100 \u00b5l of preservation medium containing sorted live cells (at a concentration of 1000-2000 cells\/\u00b5l). <\/li><\/ol><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Transfer the tubes to a swinging bucket centrifuge and spin down at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ol style = \"list-style-type: decimal;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">NOTE<\/span><span>: For centrifugation in a swinging bucket centrifuge place 1.5 ml tubes inside a 50 mL Falcon tube.<\/span><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">After centrifugation is complete, remove the medium without disrupting the pellet leaving ~20 \u00b5l of supernatant in the tube.  <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Dilute the cells with the preservation medium down to 1000-2000 cell\/\u00b5l. Use the FACS quantification as a guide, but keep in mind that these numbers are often inflated.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Gently resuspend the cells using a 1000 \u00b5l or 200 \u00b5l pipette. Do not leave cell clumps behind.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">At this step, one would typically expect to have 50-100 \u00b5l of preservation medium containing sorted live cells (at a concentration of 1000-2000 cells\/\u00b5l). <\/li><\/ol><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"1AC815E0B8A011EA9718098763077B24","order_id":2,"type_id":30,"title":"centrifuge","source":{"centrifuge":"500","duration":300,"guid":"1AC815E0B8A011EA9718098763077B24","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null,"temperature":"4","temperatureUnit":10,"unit":34}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"567F27FF442040159FAD1AA094C72D8A","order_id":3,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">NOTE: <\/span><span>When resuspending the cells in preservataion medium, make sure to avoid bubbles and do not leave any cell clumps.<\/span><\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":600,"critical":[],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":868155,"guid":"106BFDE0330411EABDAD4DE020724EBD","previous_id":868154,"previous_guid":"0B3C7A20330411EABDAD4DE020724EBD","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"7E41E5766E8A4E66B9B4513ECA241FA8","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Freezing and storage"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"530A8FC831C54FE08F2661624505C519","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><ol style = \"list-style-type: decimal;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Use slow freezing method  (\u20131\u00b0C\/minute) to freeze the cells at \u221280 \u00b0C. <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Place the tube containing cells into a isopropanol-filled container and transfer it in a \u201380 \u00b0C freezer. Isopropanol-filled containers have a stated freeze rate of \u20131\u00b0C\/minute, but performance may vary. <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">The next day, transfer the tube to liquid nitrogen tank for a long term storage.<\/li><\/ol><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#EA9F6C","section_duration":86400,"critical":[],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":969897,"guid":"47CFB9B0B8A211EA9718098763077B24","previous_id":868155,"previous_guid":"106BFDE0330411EABDAD4DE020724EBD","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"0B03AA5443FD44198DBF99DA5C6B4923","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Thawing"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"41A2F5E41C8F42409BC2C9FC290D0216","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><ol style = \"list-style-type: decimal;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Remove the tube from liquid nitrogen and transfer to water-bath set at 37 \u00baC<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Incubate the tube for 1-2 minutes, during which the frozen cells should thaw completely.<\/li><\/ol><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"D2A48FA20F3F4332ACC2976764294E8B","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">CRITICAL: <\/span><span>When thawing cells, it is of critical importance to proceed quickly, within 5-10 minutes. Handling thawed cells for longer than 15 min may result in poor quality data. <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Therefore, make sure that the scRNA-seq platform is set up and reagents are ready before starting the thawing procedure.<\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#E57785","section_duration":300,"critical":[{"id":12,"title":"Critical step","icon":"CriticalIcon"}],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":969898,"guid":"4A26D3A0B8A311EA9718098763077B24","previous_id":969897,"previous_guid":"47CFB9B0B8A211EA9718098763077B24","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"23E4E586E29D4C90ADCA7A8E3E884683","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Cell counting"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"2F39C6A6384A448DBD102C60C9C5CD31","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">1. Count the thawed cells by mixing 5 \u00b5l of cell suspension with 5 \u00b5l of 0.1% (w\/v) Trypan Blue.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">2. Evaluate cells under bright field microscopy (or alternatively, using the Countess II instrument).<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">3. Proceed to Cell Encapsulation step.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"07A85F7441F844F2B2B93BF917D1770F","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">NOTE: <\/span><span>Proceed quickly, keeping in mind that any extended incubations may result in transcriptome changes. Thawed cells can be processed directly and no buffer change is needed. <\/span><\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#EA94FF","section_duration":120,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":969947,"guid":"A771CB00B8B711EA9718098763077B24","previous_id":969898,"previous_guid":"4A26D3A0B8A311EA9718098763077B24","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"C2DED90E2AB040138DBBA7BAA977D650","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Cell Encapsulation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"28148207FC684B6CB41FF388BBCE6731","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">1. When using 10X Genomics Chromium system to perform scRNA-Seq follow the \"Cell Suspension Volume Calculator Table\" in the CG000204 RevD manual <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a href=\"https:\/\/assets.ctfassets.net\/an68im79xiti\/1eX2FPdpeCgnCJtw4fj9Hx\/7cb84edaa9eca04b607f9193162994de\/CG000204_ChromiumNextGEMSingleCell3_v3.1_Rev_D.pdf\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">here<\/span><\/a><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">2. Load the cells directly onto a chip and place the chip into the Chromium instrument.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">3. Proceed according to 10X Genomics protocol (<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a href=\"https:\/\/assets.ctfassets.net\/an68im79xiti\/1eX2FPdpeCgnCJtw4fj9Hx\/7cb84edaa9eca04b607f9193162994de\/CG000204_ChromiumNextGEMSingleCell3_v3.1_Rev_D.pdf\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">here<\/span><\/a><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">).<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"0C7263042CB04803915A150E24F6B115","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">NOTE: <\/span><span>Cells are typically washed in 1X PBS buffer + 0.04% (w\/v) BSA to remove preservation medium. However, we have found that Bambanker preservation medium does not cause detectable transcriptional changes; thus, cells should be loaded directly onto the microfluidics chip without washing or buffer exchange.  <\/span><\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":1200,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":969950,"guid":"2902EEA0B8B911EA9718098763077B24","previous_id":969947,"previous_guid":"A771CB00B8B711EA9718098763077B24","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"48D9B126961645ABB659FC704D96053A","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"scRNA-Seq"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"0AF1A072A628405A82245036874ACF7E","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">1. Follow the 10X Genomics manual CG000204 RevD <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a href=\"https:\/\/assets.ctfassets.net\/an68im79xiti\/1eX2FPdpeCgnCJtw4fj9Hx\/7cb84edaa9eca04b607f9193162994de\/CG000204_ChromiumNextGEMSingleCell3_v3.1_Rev_D.pdf\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">here<\/span><\/a><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> to construct the scRNA-Seq library.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">2. We use a NovaSeq 6000 instrument to sequence the final DNA libraries using pair-end sequencing option, R1 read - 26 cycles, R2 read - 70 cycles, and index read - 8 cycles, aiming for \u223c150M reads per ~5,000 single-cells.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">3. We process FASQ files using the <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a href=\"https:\/\/github.com\/ambrosejcarr\/seqc\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">SEQC<\/span><\/a><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> pipeline and mapped to a reference genome with the default SEQC parameters to obtain the gene-cell count matrices. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":172800,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":970131,"guid":"FA582B40B93C11EA9718098763077B24","previous_id":969950,"previous_guid":"2902EEA0B8B911EA9718098763077B24","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"5C801F37B8364EB4AE303149A206F042","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Expected results"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"3CF0A5DEA3484C38821FF1BE8E6C12DB","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">To evaluate how the freezing\/thawing procedure affects cellular transcriptomes, we performed scRNA-seq on cells derived from human lung. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">We dissociated fresh human lung tissue into a single-cell suspension (step 1), we FACS-sorted live cells (steps 2-6), and divided the sorted live cells we collected into three tubes with equal volumes:<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Tube 1<\/span><span>. Cells were processed for scRNA-Seq immediately following 10X Genomics manual CG000204 RevD <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a href=\"https:\/\/assets.ctfassets.net\/an68im79xiti\/1eX2FPdpeCgnCJtw4fj9Hx\/7cb84edaa9eca04b607f9193162994de\/CG000204_ChromiumNextGEMSingleCell3_v3.1_Rev_D.pdf\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">here<\/span><\/a><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Tube 2<\/span><span>. The preservation medium in which cells were suspended was replaced with RPMI 1640 by centrifugation at 400 g for 5 min, and processed for scRNA-seq in parallel with Tube 1. <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Tube 3. <\/span><span>FACS-sorted cells were frozen (step 5) and incubated in liquid nitrogen for 2 weeks. Next, cells were thawed, counted and processed for scRNA-Seq (steps 6-9).<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">The results are summarized in Figures 1-2 below:  <\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/46f6f8548d2ca7bd45974787b99085bf3dfaad0323b3393bf43fd0dd5b858d45\/cdt3i2ue.png\" \/><\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/46f6f8548d2ca7bd45974787b99085bf3dfaad0323b3393bf43fd0dd5b858d45\/cc9ki2ue.png\" \/><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"00E8C823FC454300825EFADC52D77275","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/46f6f8548d2ca7bd45974787b99085bf3dfaad0323b3393bf43fd0dd5b858d45\/cdt3i2ue.png\" \/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"49B66DAD7D1843218F8EC179B0AB0565",